\begin{frame}{Groundwater Flow Equations}
  Darcy's Law relates groundwater discharge (Q) to hydraulic conductivity (K), hydraulic gradient (I), and cross section area (A) that groundwater flows through: 
  \begin{equation*}
    Q=-K \cdot A \cdot I
  \end{equation*}
  Rearranging Darcy's Law:
  \begin{equation*}
    K=\frac{-Q}{A \cdot I}
  \end{equation*}

  Darcy created this law based on observations of water flowing through a column of sediments. In this lab, a Darcy Tube will be used to calculate the hydraulic conductivity, a measure of permeability, of silty sand.
\end{frame}

